OL,5, Donald Trump has been told to pay the  
OL,6, six-figure legal costs of a company he 
OL,7, sued over claims of "perverted" sex    
OL,8, acts and bribes to Russian officials.  
OL,10,FMrs Justice Steyn threw out the case   
OL,11,Fagainst Orbis Business Intelligence, a 
OL,12,Fconsultancy founded by former MI6      
OL,13,Fofficer Christopher Steele, last month.
OL,15,FShe found that Mr Trump's compensation 
OL,16,Fclaim was "bound to fail".             
OL,18,FIn a new ruling she also ordered Mr    
OL,19,FTrump to pay Orbis's costs "of the     
OL,20,Fentire claim".                         
